121 "§41-6-4
122 (a) The board of trustees shall fill all vacancies
123 occurring on the board, whether by expiration of term of
124 service or by death or resignation, but the The names of all
125 successor newly appointed board members shall be communicated
126 to the then current session or the next ensuing regular
127 session of the state Senate for confirmation. If the Senate
128 rejects any successor trusteeappointed member, the board
129 appointing authority shall proceed forthwith to fill the
130 vacancy with a different appointee.
131 (b) A trustee An individual appointed to succeed a
132 member whose term has expired shall serve for a term of six
133 years. A person An individual appointed to fill a vacancy
134 occurring by death or, resignation, or removal shall only
135 serve out the unexpired term of his or her predecessor. A
136 person whose appointment to the board has been confirmed by
137 the Senate shall serve beyond his or her expired term until a
138 successor has been confirmed by the Senate.
139 (c) The board shall hold at the State Capital at least
140 one regular meeting during every year and as many special
Page 5

one regular meeting during every year and as many special
HB169 INTRODUCED
141 meetings as may be necessary, and at any meeting. a A majority
142 of the trustees board members shall constitute a quorum. The
143 Governor of the state, or his or her designee, shall be a
144 voting member of the board as authorized by Section 41-6-3,
145 and he or she shall, as far as possible, shall lend every
146 encouragement to the success and upbuilding development of the
147 department. The director shall be the secretary of the board.
148 The trustees Members of the board shall receive no
149 compensation for their services. Each member of the board of
150 trustees shall be reimbursed at the same per diem and travel
151 allowance amounts paid by law to state employees for each day
152 of attendance of the business of the board.
153 (d) The board may do all of the following:
154 (1) Adopt rules for its own government and also for the
155 government of the department.
156 (2) Elect a director and provide for the selection or
157 appointment of other officials or employees as may be
158 authorized.
159 (3) Provide for the publication of historical material
160 pertaining to the state under the supervision of the director.
161 (4) Control and expend such appropriations as may be
162 made for the maintenance of the department.
163 (5) Perform such other acts as may be necessary to
164 carry out the intent and purposes of this article."
165 Section 2. This act shall be retroactive to January 1,
166 2025.
167 Section 3. This act shall become effective immediately.
